Parliament’s Joint Committee on Ethics and Members’ Interests has published the register of members’ interests for 2021. The register is published to ensure transparency, and to instil public trust and confidence in parliament, with members required to declare significant holdings in businesses, shares owned, as well as gifts received. With the full register now available to the public, BusinessTech looked at some of South Africa’s most prominent politicians and what they declared. Deputy president – David Mabuza <img class="size-full wp-image-425004 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/DavidMabuza1-e1597303468479.png" alt="" width="640" height="429" /> Business Directorship/partnership in Nelesco;
